description: Git commit conventions and performance constraints for the background service and UI
alwaysApply: true
---

# Git Rules

- Commit messages: `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `refactor:`, `ui:`
- Never commit commented-out code
- Never commit debug prints
- Each feature should be on its own branch

# Performance Rules

- Background service checks foreground app every 500ms — do not reduce below this
- Dispose all controllers and listeners in dispose()
- Use lazy loading for the installed apps list (can be 100+ apps)
- Cache app icons after first load — do not reload on every render
